edu.stanford.nlp.ling.tokensregex.matcher

Class TrieMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<Iterable<K>,V>
      • edu.stanford.nlp.ling.tokensregex.matcher.TrieMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<Iterable<K>,V>

    public class TrieMap<K,V>
extends AbstractMap<Iterable<K>,V>
    Map that takes a iterable as key, and maps it to an value. This implementation is not particularly memory efficient, but will have relatively fast lookup times for sequences where there are many possible keys (e.g. sequences over Strings) Can be used for fairly efficient look up of sequence by prefix
    Author:
    Angel Chang
